radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal subsegmental atelectasis at the left lung base. No focal consolidation or pleural effusion. Liver demonstrates homogeneous parenchymal enhancement without suspicious focal lesion. Gallbladder has a small amount of sludge or stones, otherwise normal. Mild heterogeneous enhancement of the pancreatic head without suggestion of mass lesion. Normal spleen and adrenal glands. Symmetric enhancement and excretion from both kidneys without suspicious focal lesion or hydronephrosis. Normal abdominal aorta and branch vessels. Stomach and small bowel loops normal without evidence of obstruction or inflammation. No abdominal free fluid or free air. Normal appendix. Rectum and colon normal without evidence of obstruction or inflammation. Bladder mildly distended and appears normal.
